# # 📊 Tech Jobs Dataset — Stage 3: Visualizations

# Now that we've explored the raw data, it's time to **see** it. Charts reveal patterns that numbers alone can't show — skewed distributions, outliers, clear category gaps.

# This notebook covers **10 visualizations** grouped by what they answer:

# | # | Chart | Question answered |
# |---|-------|------------------|
# | 1 | Salary histogram | What does the salary distribution look like? |
# | 2 | Salary by experience (boxplot) | Does seniority actually pay more? |
# | 3 | Salary by work mode (boxplot) | Do remote workers earn more? |
# | 4 | Top countries by job count (bar) | Where are the most jobs? |
# | 5 | Average salary by country (bar) | Where does the highest pay come from? |
# | 6 | Job role distribution (horizontal bar) | Which roles dominate? |
# | 7 | Salary by company size (boxplot) | Does company size affect pay? |
# | 8 | Records per year (line) | How has hiring changed over time? |
# | 9 | Work mode breakdown (pie) | Remote vs hybrid vs onsite split? |
# | 10 | Correlation heatmap | Which numeric columns move together? |

